user.biography: WHERE ANIMALS COME FIRST ❤️ Brolga & Tahnee - wildlife carers 🦘We rescue & raise orphaned kangaroos. Meet our roos on tour. Home of Kangaroo Dundee 🦘

node.text:
Thanks for all your kindness to us Aussies. Please visit us. We can’t wait to see you 🧡

Repost: @australia ❤️
We want to send our mates around the world a big thank you for all your love and support. We hope you will come visit soon!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Kangaroo Sanctuary 🦘 in Alice Springs, Northern Territory. May be an image of animal and outdoors.

node.text: Our lovely 13 year old Naomi, greying around her face from beautiful old age.♥️ Naomi came to us as a tiny orphaned baby after a tour guide found her all alone near a remote fence line.

node.text: Darling Ferris loves being cuddled on our sunset tour 🌅🦘 Repost from @frenchies_trippers Go to @thekangaroosanctuary discovering how take care of Joeys and learning about kangaroos lifestyle with Brolga. 💯

node.text: Different species Elizabeth and Pip are best friends. 💕 They are always snuggling in their pouches and playing together when outside for their hops. Elizabeth is an Eastern Grey Kangaroo and Pip is a Red Kangaroo.
